Bashir Ahmed, the Personal Assistant to President Muhammadu Buhari on New Media, has urged Nigerians to disregard reports that President Muhammadu Buhari’s Nephew, Mamman Daura had been flown to London for urgent medical attention. Daura, who is a close confidant of Buhari was reportedly flown abroad for medical care last week. He was alleged to have renal problems. Reacting in a tweet on Saturday, Bashir said there was no iota of truth in the report as Daura is hale and hearty. Alongside a video of Daura, Bashir wrote, “No iota of truth in the earlier story that Mallam Mamman Daura was flown to London for an emergency medical attention. “He is hale and hearty. Nigerians should disregard that story.” See video below… No iota of truth in the earlier story that Mallam Mamman Daura was flown to London for an emergency medical attention, he is hale and hearty, Nigerians should disregard that story. pic.twitter.com/6CJMwnDDlD Source The family of Mamman Daura, President Muhammadu Buhari’s nephew have confirmed that he traveld to the UK, but said he is “in good health”. A family source confirmed this to the TheCable. There are social media reports that the former journalist and industrialist had been infected with COVID-19 and was… August 20, 2020 In "News" President Muhammadu Buhari's nephew, Mamman Daura, 79 was flown abroad on Wednesday August 19, for an urgent medical treatment after exhibiting symptoms similar to Coronavirus, according to SaharaReporters. The publication added that Daura was flown to the United Kingdom. “Daura, 79, was said to have been flown in a private… August 20, 2020 In "Politics" Daura    -    A sister in-law to President Muhammadu Buhari, Hajiya Aisha Mamman, is dead. Mamman, 75, died in the early hours of Thursday. The Information Officer of the Daura Local Government Council in Katsina, Alhaji Salisu Haro, made the disclosure in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in… February 8, 2018 In "News"